PRIVACY POLICY
PRIVACY POLICY
PRIMAVERA SOUND GLOBAL PRIVACY POLICY
This privacy policy (the "
Privacy Policy
") describes how we collect, use, store, share and protect the personal data provided by users (the "
Users
" or "
User
") through the website (the “
Website
”) and in the framework of the relationship that the Users enter into with us when they purchase a ticket or pass for any of the festivals organized by Primavera Sound, S.L.
Your personal data will be processed in strict compliance with General Data Protection Regulation (EU) 679/2016 ( the "
GDPR
"), Spanish
Data Protection Act
[
Ley Orgánica 3/2018 de Protección de Datos Personales y garantía de los derechos digitales
] and any other applicable regulations.
As a User, you warrant: (a) the authenticity and veracity of all the data you communicate; (b) that they are your personal data or that you have the data subject's permission to use them; (c) and that you will keep the information provided up to date, ensuring that it responds at all times to the actual situation, and you are solely responsible for any false or inaccurate representations you make, and for any losses that may arise from this.
This Privacy Policy is available in Spanish, Catalan, Portuguese, and English.
1. Who is the data controller?
The data controller of your personal data is the Spanish company PRIMAVERA SOUND S.L., with tax identification number B61978987 and corporate address at C/ Josep Pla 2, Torre B1, Planta 7, 08019 Barcelona (España) (“
Primavera Sound
”) or “
we.
”
2. Who is the data protection officer?
The data protection officer acts as a liaison between Primavera Sound and you, to ensure Primavera Sound’s compliance with the data protection legislation and guarantee your rights under such legislation. You can contact the data protection officer of Primavera Sound at
privacy@primaverasound.com
.
3. For which purposes does Primavera Sound process your personal data and what categories of personal data does it use for each?
Concerning the Primavera Sound Festival organized by Primavera Sound, S.L. (jointly, the “
Festival
”), Primavera Sound processes your personal data for the following purposes:
a. When you have purchased tickets through our Website, to (i) process your order, (ii) receive and process your payment, (iii) provide customer support in relation to the tickets or passes purchased and (iv) any other activity related to the selling of tickets.
For these purposes, Primavera Sound will need to process your identification and contact data (e.g., your first name and surnames, date of birth, telephone number and email and postal address) and your financial and payment data.
b. Send you commercial communications that contain information about the Festival or any other upcoming events, products or services related to the Festival (such as transport or accommodation services), as well as other Primavera Sound festivals that take place in other cities.
To allow you to receive this information, we will process your identification and contact data (specifically, your full name and email address).
c. Send you customer support e-mails or information about your status as a user, which may include, among others, reservation confirmations, event reminders or event modifications and information concerning the access to the venue.
As part of this, we will also process your identification and contact data, as well as the information related to the specific Festival you are attending and to which the relevant communication pertains.
d. Guarantee the security and safety of the festival premises, assets and individuals and, if applicable, to investigate any possible incidents that may take place during the festival. This may include video surveillance systems.
The categories of personal data that Primavera Sound will need to process for these purposes will depend on the applicable purpose in each case; e.g., the incident that has occurred or the means used to guarantee the security of the facilities as well as providing the necessary mobility adaptations for users who need them. Your identification and contact details, your image or health documentation in the case of persons with reduced mobility and/or special needs may, inter alia, be processed.
e. If platforms or social networks such as Spotify, Google and Facebook that compile your personal data as data controllers obtain your consent (when they are legally required to do so) to share those data with us, we will process them so that Primavera Sound can obtain information on your consumption on those media and your preferences in terms of artists when using those social platforms, and send you, if you have asked for it, additional, adapted commercial information that may be of interest to you. In addition to this information, Primavera Sound will need to process your identification and contact data, as indicated above, for this purpose.
f. In relation to the Primavera Sound festivals that take place in different cities and are organized by third parties, to properly manage them and allow us to evaluate the performance of those festivals and identify which are the modifications that need to be introduced in order to offer a better experience to the festival-goers.
Furthermore, when accessing to Primavera Sound Website and mobile application, Primavera Sound processes your personal data for the following purposes:
g. Whenever you sign up for a Primavera Sound account via our Website  or in one of our apps, to manage your account or any of the applications available in the referred website (for instance, the “Primavera Sound Forum” section). If it applies to you, in relation to the processing of your data specifically performed in the framework of the AccessTicket application, you can find detailed information in the
AccessTicket Privacy Policy.
h. To respond to your requests of information and/or suggestions made through the “Contact Form” available at the Website and/or in the relevant Primaversa Sound apps.
In both cases,  Primavera Sound may process the following categories of personal data: your identification and contact data (including first name and surnames), date of birth, gender, national identification document or corresponding official identity document, email and postal address, telephone number and, where applicable, your photograph); user account data (such as your username and password or the information on interactions or tickets or passes uploaded to your account; information relating to your entry to the Festival when using the relevant application; or the personal information that may be included in the requests, suggestions or communications you send us.
i. Permit, manage, analyze, and apply improvements in the browsing of the Website by Users. For more information on this purpose, see our
Cookies Policy.
Finally, Primavera Sound will process your personal data to guarantee compliance with the legal obligations to which it is subject, and it must process the categories of personal data necessary in each case in view of the applicable legislation.
4. Which are the lawful bases to process your personal data?
Processing activities indicated under Section 3 (a), (e), (f), (g) and (h): the fulfillment of our contract with you (and, in particular, our Terms and Conditions) when purchasing the tickets to attend the Primavera Sound Festival or when you create an account in our website, or, as applicable, the application of the precontractual measures that may be appropriate.
To send the commercial communications outlined in Section 3 (b), the consent given by you when checking the checkbox available on the website, although for current customers some commercial communications could also be sent based on the legitimate interest of Primavera Sound. Your express consent will also be the legal basis for processing information about your media consumption and artist preferences described in Section 3 (e).
Processing activities under Section 3 (d), and (e): the legitimate interest of Primavera Sound in processing your personal data for the purposes indicated in the referred sections. In this respect, we consider that the mentioned legitimate interest, on which Primavera Sound bases the processing of your personal data, does respect your fundamental rights and freedoms since your personal data is being processed to improve as a company and offer attendees to the Primavera Sound a better experience at their festivals. For more information on the processing of your data, you write to
privacy@primaverasound.com
.
In countries located outside the European Union where the legitimate interest is not a legal basis for processing personal data, by accepting this Privacy Policy you will be granting your express consent to all the processing activities listed under Section 3 (c), (d) and (e).
5. How long Primavera Sound will retain your personal data?
Primavera Sound will process your personal data as long as:
a. You do not object to the reception of Primavera Sound commercial communications and, if you have objected, for as long as necessary to attend your request to no longer receive said informative alerts;
b. The purposes for which the personal data is processed are being achieved.
Once those periods have elapsed, Primavera Sound must retain your personal data, duly blocked,  until the end of the statues of limitation of any liabilities that may arise and during the term required to comply with any applicable legal obligation.
6. With whom does Primavera Sound share your personal data?
Primavera Sound will only share your personal data when it is legally or contractually required to do so. Specifically, your personal data may be shared with:
a. Providers of products and services hired by Primavera Sound as data processors, to achieve the mentioned purposes, such as reception and security services of the premises, maintenance services for video surveillance or IT and cloud services.
b. Local Organizers in charge of the management of each specific festival, as data processors. Your personal data will only be shared with them in the event Primavera Sound deems it necessary, so the Local Organizers can carry out specific commercial communications.
c. Competent authorities as well as other third parties interested in investigating an illegal act and, if applicable, establishing, exercising or defending the actions or claims always fulfilling the applicable legal requirements.
Furthermore, Primavera Sound may share your personal data with other companies of the Primavera Sound group, for internal administration purposes or, if you have consented, for commercial purposes.
Should your personal data be accessed from countries that do not provide an adequate level of protection, Primavera Sound will, if necessary, take appropriate safeguards to carry out such international data transfers in accordance with applicable data protection legislation.
7. Which are your rights when you provide us with your personal data?
As a data subject, you may exercise any of the following rights established in the applicable legislation:
Access: you may access your data included in Primavera Sound files.
Rectification/Modification: you may modify your personal data if these are inaccurate.
Erasure: you may request that your personal data are erased.
Objection: you may request that your personal data are not processed.
Portability: you may receive, in an electronic file, the personal data that you provided Primavera Sound with, as well as send it to different entities.
Restriction of processing: you may request a restriction on how your data is processed when: (i) the accuracy of your personal data is being verified after you have contested its accuracy, (ii) the processing of your data is illegal and you oppose to the erasure of your data; (iii) Primavera Sound does no longer need the personal data for the purposes of the processing, but they are required by you for the establishment, exercise or defense of legal claims, (iv) you have objected to the processing for the performance of a task carried out in the public interest or necessary for the purposes of a legitimate interest, whilst it is being verified whether the legitimate grounds of Primavera Sound override yours.
Opt-Out: you can request to stop receiving our promotional emails by following the instructions in any marketing email you get from us. You can also change your preferences in your account. It may take some days to process your request. You can also reiterate your consent given for a specific processing activity at any time, following the indicated procedure.
Furthermore, data subjects located in
Brazil
also have the following data subject rights:
Confirmation: you may ask for confirmation of the existence of the processing.
Information about the possibility of denying consent and the consequences of such denial.
Right to petition concerning your personal data, against Primavera Sound before the national authority.
Right to request a review of decisions made solely on the basis of automated processing, when applicable.
Information about public and private entities with whom we share your data, when applicable.
Concerning the right of objection indicated above, to request that your personal data are not processed when based on one of the situation of waiver consent, if there is non-compliance with the provisions of the applicable law.
Request the anonymization, blocking or erasure of your personal data, insofar as it is considered unnecessary, excessive or non-compliant.
Additionally, at any time, you may withdraw your consent without affecting the data processing carried out before such withdrawal. In order to exercise your rights and/or withdraw your consent, you can send your request to
privacy@primaverasound.com
, duly identifying yourself and stating the right you wish to exercise. If Primavera Sound has reasonable doubts about your identity it may request additional information to deal with your request with total security.
In any case, you also have the right to lodge a complaint before the Spanish Data Protection Authority (
www.aepd.es
) or the competent data protection authority in your country of residence.
8. Changes in the Privacy Policy
Primavera Sound reserves the right to amend this Privacy Policy as a result of new personal data processing or modification of existing processing methods, and based on new legislative or regulatory requirements, for security reasons or to adapt the policy to the data protection instructions of supervisory authorities or to new processes.
Whenever there are significant changes to this Privacy Policy, Primavera Sound will duly inform all Users so that they have the chance to review the changes and, if necessary, accept them before they take effect.
9. Contact
For any questions or queries regarding this Privacy Policy, do not hesitate to contact us using the forms on the Website, or contact our DPO by sending an email to
privacy@primaverasound.com
.
